/!\ IMPORTANT /!\ 
------------------
In order to test the project locally (on your machine) you MUST install
a web server and a PHP environment. 
We recommand you to install the Apache Web server and PHP 5.3+



1) SVN repository
2) ZIP Install
3) Online demo

1) SVN repository:
------------------
You can grab and install the ACO Editor directly from the SVN by simply typing this command
on your command line (you must have installed the subversion application before!):
	
	svn checkout http://acoprojet.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ acoprojet
	cd acoprojet/


2) ZIP Install:
---------------
A zipped version is hosted at http://acoeditor.cheghamwassim.com/acoeditor_v3.zip
To download it, you can use the wget programm as the following:

	wget http://acoeditor.cheghamwassim.com/acoeditor_v3.zip
	unzip acoeditor_3.zip
	cd acoeditor_v3/


3) Online demo:
---------------
If you don't care about insatlling the acoeditor and want just to demo the app. Please 
visit the official webpage at http://acoeditor.cheghamwassim.com
